qas.question: New York is home to what largest transportation system in the world?
What types of fires can start in parks and woodlands?

context: The New York City Fire Department faces highly multifaceted firefighting challenges in many ways unique to New York. In addition to responding to building types that range from wood-frame single family homes to high-rise structures, there are many secluded bridges and tunnels, as well as large parks and wooded areas that can give rise to <a1_0>brush fires<a1_0/>. New York is also home to one of the largest <a0_0>subway systems<a0_0/> in the world, consisting of hundreds of miles of tunnel with electrified track.
